The paper discusses the benefits and challenges of massive MIMO systems, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses upper layer techniques for incorporating massive MIMO in network deployment scenarios, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the potential for using machine learning (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in future research, indicating that these sub-categories are also relevant.
